  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nI was browsing through the lighthouse code and it looks like the `debug-level` cli option might have the wrong help text:\r\n\r\n**code:**\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/869b0621d6f51e98473bb67cec0446d3623b8957/lighthouse/src/main.rs#L59-L62\r\n\r\n**cli:**\r\n```\r\n$ ./lighthouse --help\r\nLighthouse 0.2.0\r\nSigma Prime <contact@sigmaprime.io>\r\nEthereum 2.0 client by Sigma Prime. Provides a full-featured beacon node, a validator client and utilities for managing\r\nvalidator accounts.\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n    lighthouse [OPTIONS] [SUBCOMMAND]\r\n\r\nFLAGS:\r\n    -h, --help       Prints help information\r\n    -V, --version    Prints version information\r\n\r\nOPTIONS:\r\n    -d, --datadir <DIR>          Data directory for lighthouse keys and databases.\r\n        --debug-level <LEVEL>    The title of the spec constants for chain config. [default: info]  [possible values:\r\n                                 info, debug, trace, warn, error, crit]\r\n        --log-format <FORMAT>    Specifies the format used for logging. [possible values: JSON]\r\n        --logfile <FILE>         File path where output will be written. Default file logging format is JSON.\r\n    -s, --spec <TITLE>           Specifies the default eth2 spec type. [default: mainnet]  [possible values: mainnet,\r\n                                 minimal, interop]\r\n\r\nSUBCOMMANDS:\r\n    account_manager     Utilities for generating and managing Ethereum 2.0 accounts. [aliases: a, am, account,\r\n                        account_manager]\r\n    beacon_node         The primary component which connects to the Ethereum 2.0 P2P network and downloads, verifies\r\n                        and stores blocks. Provides a HTTP API for querying the beacon chain and publishing messages\r\n                        to the network. [aliases: b, bn, beacon]\r\n    help                Prints this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\r\n    validator_client    When connected to a beacon node, performs the duties of a staked validator (e.g., proposing\r\n                        blocks and attestations). [aliases: v, vc, validator]\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
